{"priority": "major", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/use-brew-bottle-more-and-host-bottles-at"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray", "component": {"name": "os::osx", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/components/399529.json"}}}, "votes": 0, "watches": 1, "content": {"raw": "There are some useful recommendations in [this homebrew comment](https://github.com/Homebrew/brew/issues/2572#issuecomment-298874118):\r\n\r\n* tap maintainers should be able to push to a pull request branch, so we should be able to build bottles even if the `osrfbuild` fork wasn't used\r\n\r\n* use `brew bottle --write` and `brew bottle --merge` instead of our [current sed command](#!/osrf/release-tools/src/389b041e0bb18b3361c17d6707d2d3537eb6efec/jenkins-scripts/lib/homebrew_bottle_pullrequest.bash?at=default&fileviewer=file-view-default#homebrew_bottle_pullrequest.bash-83)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>There are some useful recommendations in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://github.com/Homebrew/brew/issues/2572#issuecomment-298874118\" rel=\"nofollow\">this homebrew comment</a>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>tap maintainers should be able to push to a pull request branch, so we should be able to build bottles even if the <code>osrfbuild</code> fork wasn't used</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>use <code>brew bottle --write</code> and <code>brew bottle --merge</code> instead of our <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/release-tools/src/389b041e0bb18b3361c17d6707d2d3537eb6efec/jenkins-scripts/lib/homebrew_bottle_pullrequest.bash?at=default&amp;fileviewer=file-view-default#homebrew_bottle_pullrequest.bash-83\" rel=\"nofollow\">current sed command</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2017-05-04T21:14:50.732762+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2018-10-16T19:29:43.084616+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 109}